The little triangle (of base b and height 1.25-h) is formed by the air on the right side of the tank. It is a similar triangle to the triangle of base 3 and height 1.25, so \frac{b}{1.25-h}&=\frac{3}{1.25}
b&=\frac{3}{1.25}(1.25-h)
